All is now set at the Murtala Mohammed International Airport, for the commencement of international flights tomorrow. The Deputy Governor of Lagos State, Dr. Obafemi Hamzat and the Managing Director of the Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN), Captain Rabiu Yadudu made this known in an interview with newsmen after an inspection of facilities at the airport where flights had been suspended since March this year to curb the spread of COVID-19.  Dr. Hamzat who was accompanied by some members of the Lagos State Executive Council said the airport is fully ready to receive international flights in compliance with Covid-19 protocols.Â  The Lagos State Deputy Governor also reiterated the State's Government's readiness to support FAAN, and appealed to travellers to obey all directives issued to ensure their safety.  On his part, Captain Yadudu stated that three airliners are being expected at MMIA tomorrow with the first flight expected to land at about 2 o'clock in the afternoon. Our Correspondent Immanuel Odeyemi quotes the FAAN Managing Director as saying that adequate arrangements have also been made at MMIA to ensure the comfort of physically challenged passengers.